{
  "slug": "feedback-works-best-when-it-is-specific",
  "title": "Feedback works best when it is specific",
  "category": "leadership",
  "kicker": "Team communication",
  "hook": "Vague feedback makes people anxious. Specific feedback gives them a handle.",
  "readMinutes": 5,
  "date": "2026-06-20",
  "tags": [
    "feedback",
    "coaching"
  ],
  "beats": [
    {
      "num": "01 · the shape",
      "heading": "Good job is nice, not useful",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Praise and critique both need detail. Without the situation, behavior, and impact, the person cannot repeat the good part or change the rough part.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "terminal",
          "title": "manager · feedback draft",
          "caption": "The useful signal is usually already there.",
          "lines": [
            {
              "t": "situation: design review Tuesday",
              "c": ""
            },
            {
              "t": "behavior: you named the risk and offered two paths",
              "c": ""
            },
            {
              "t": "impact: the team made a decision in the room",
              "c": ""
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "02 · the move",
      "heading": "Anchor it in observable behavior",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Describe what happened, why it mattered, and what to continue or adjust. Keep identity out of it. Focus on behavior the person can control.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "file": "feedback.txt",
          "code": "When the API debate stalled,\nyou wrote the two tradeoffs on the board.\nThat helped the team choose a path.\nPlease keep doing that in ambiguous reviews.",
          "caption": "Specific praise teaches the behavior you want repeated."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "03 · the check",
      "heading": "Give feedback while it is fresh",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Feedback decays. A tiny note this week beats a dramatic monologue three months from now.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "stats",
          "items": [
            {
              "to": 3,
              "label": "parts: situation, behavior, impact"
            },
            {
              "to": 1,
              "label": "clear next action"
            },
            {
              "to": 0,
              "label": "personality diagnoses"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "04 · the takeaway",
      "heading": "Clarity is respect",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Specific feedback lowers the emotional tax because it turns a cloudy judgment into a workable observation.</p>"
        },
